ol.li:
It shall be lawful for the Landlord to re-enter the Premises and the tenancy hereby created shall absolutely determine id:-
a) the Charges or any other sum payable by the Tenant to the Landlord shall at any time remain unpaid for 14 days or if the Landlord is unsuccessful in making 3 GIRO deductions;
b) a term here in shall not be performed by the Tenant within 10 days of being served a written notice by the Landlord;
c) the Tenant shall make an assignment for the benefit of creditors or enter into an arrangement with creditors by composition or otherwise or suffer any distress or attachment or execution to be levied against their goods;and
d)the Tenant, being a company, shall enter into liquidation, whether compulsory or voluntary, save for the purpose of reconstruction or amalgamation, or, being an individual, shall commit an act of bankruptcy or have a bankruptcy order made against the Tenant.
